    52	## Smoke Run
    53	
    54	Task 027 adds a bounded smoke script for the complete front-camera bridge path:
    55	
    56	```bash
    57	bash scripts/smoke_vision_bridge.sh
    58	```
    59	
    60	The script checks:
    61	
    62	- local model, world, bridge config, and ArUco texture assets;
    63	- Gazebo publication of the configured camera image topic;
    64	- `ros_gz_bridge` package availability;
    65	- ROS 2 availability of `/vision/front/image_raw`;
    66	- target pose publication on `/vision/target_pose`.
    67	
    68	When `ros_gz_bridge` is available and the image stream produces a frame, the
    69	script writes:
    70	
    71	```text
    72	visualizations/demo_07_camera/<timestamp>/sample_frame.png
    73	```
    74	
    75	If a live frame cannot be captured, the same output directory contains
    76	`sample_frame_status.txt` with the bounded-check reason.
    77	
    78	The lower-level manual sequence is still useful for interactive debugging in a
    79	sourced ROS 2 environment:
    80	
    81	```bash
    82	src/aerial_manip_gazebo/scripts/smoke_load_x500_arm_2dof.sh
    83	ros2 launch aerial_manip_gazebo front_camera_bridge.launch.py
    84	ros2 topic hz /vision/front/image_raw
    85	```
    86	
    87	If `ros_gz_bridge` is not installed, the package can still build, but runtime
    88	image bridging is unavailable until the ROS/Gazebo bridge package is installed.
    89	The smoke script reports this as `WARN` and does not substitute placeholder
    90	target data for the live image checks.
    63	## Detector and Placeholder Modes
    64	
    65	The active Python environment exposes OpenCV ArUco support, so the default node
    66	uses `cv2.aruco.detectMarkers` and `cv2.aruco.estimatePoseSingleMarkers`.
    67	
    68	If camera bridging or detector support is unavailable, run:
    69	
    70	```bash
    71	ros2 launch aerial_manip_vision tag_target_pose.launch.py publish_placeholder:=true
    72	```
    73	
    74	Placeholder mode publishes the documented static target pose at
    75	`[2.0, 0.0, 0.5]` in `uav/base_link` and the corresponding relative pose in
    76	`uav/camera_link`. This is a wiring smoke test only; it is not a visual
    77	detection result.
    78	
    79	The Task 027 smoke script keeps this distinction explicit. Live checks launch
    80	the node with `publish_placeholder:=false`; if no detected pose appears before
    81	the timeout, the script reports `WARN` and writes
    82	`live_target_pose_status.txt`. Placeholder mode is launched separately only to
    83	verify the ROS topic wiring path.
